#. type: Content of: <guide><title>
#: en/gpm.xml:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using a Mouse within the Console"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><abstract>
#: en/gpm.xml:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This guide shows you how to set up and use GPM (the General Purpose Mouse\n"
"server) from within a command line interface. This is especially useful for new\n"
"Gentoo installations or for systems that cannot or do not use an X server.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/gpm.xml:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "Getting GPM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:31
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you've just installed Gentoo, you almost certainly don't have your mouse set\n"
"up to work within a command line interface (CLI) yet. Or perhaps you can't use\n"
"or don't need an X server, yet you still need to use a mouse. The solution is\n"
"simple: <c>gpm</c>, the General Purpose Mouse server.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:38
#, no-wrap
msgid "First, you will need to get GPM:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining GPM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge gpm</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:46
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You might have noticed a few messages during the compilation that warned about\n"
"configuring the server. You must do this before starting GPM.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/gpm.xml:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring GPM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:60
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Before you can use GPM, you will need to uncomment the lines corresponding to\n"
"the location and protocol of your mouse. You do this by editing the GPM\n"
"configuration file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up GPM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>nano /etc/conf.d/gpm</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:70
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In my case, I have a USB mouse on <path>/dev/input/mouse0</path>. So, I have\n"
"uncommented <path>/dev/input/mice</path>, as this is the cumulative device for\n"
"all mice on the system, and the appropriate protocol. Try using\n"
"<path>/dev/input/mice</path> before <path>/dev/psaux</path>, as the latter is\n"
"deprecated and can be disabled in the latest 2.6 kernels. If\n"
"<path>/dev/input/mice</path> fails, then fall back to other devices. Here is my\n"
"example <path>/etc/conf.d/gpm</path>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example GPM config"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:80
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Please uncomment the type of mouse you have and the appropriate MOUSEDEV entry)</comment>\n"
"\n"
"#MOUSE=ps2\n"
"MOUSE=imps2\n"
"#MOUSEDEV=/dev/psaux\n"
"MOUSEDEV=/dev/input/mice\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:89
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have a wheelmouse, you will want to use the imps2 protocol, so uncomment\n"
"that line. If imps2 and ps2 both fail to work for you, please refer to the GPM\n"
"info page (<c>info gpm</c>) for other protocols to try. Also, if you want to be\n"
"able to click on hyperlinks in terminals to navigate to a website, it is a good\n"
"idea to follow the suggestion in the <c>/etc/conf.d/gpm</c> file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "Other options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:97
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Please uncomment this line if you want GPM to understand charsets\n"
"used in URLs and names with ~ or : in them, etc.\n"
"This is a good idea to turn on!)</comment>\n"
"\n"
"APPEND=\"-l \\\"a-zA-Z0-9_.:~/\\300-\\326\\330-\\366\\370-\\377\\\"\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:105
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The rest of the conf.d file contains other suggestions for your mouse server;\n"
"uncomment the various options according to your needs. See <c>man gpm</c> for\n"
"more information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/gpm.xml:115
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running GPM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:120
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that your mouse server is installed and configured, it's time to start\n"
"using it:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:124
#, no-wrap
msgid "The GPM init script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>/etc/init.d/gpm start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:129
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You should see a block cursor appear. Remember that only root can run the GPM\n"
"init script. However, to avoid having to <c>su</c> and run the script every\n"
"single time you begin a new session, why not set GPM to begin every time you\n"
"turn on your computer?\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:135
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding GPM to the default runlevel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:136
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>rc-update add gpm default</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:140
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now, whenever you start your computer, you'll be greeted by the console cursor\n"
"by the time you get to the login prompt. The mouse server will continue to run\n"
"even if you're not logged in as root.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/gpm.xml:150
#, no-wrap
msgid "Working with GPM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gpm.xml:152
#, no-wrap
msgid "Copying and pasting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:156
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Copying and pasting large blocks of text with a working mouse server is very\n"
"easy. Simply highlight the text with the left mouse button (it will stay\n"
"highlighted when you release the button), switch to a different terminal if you\n"
"wish, position the cursor, and press the middle mouse button to paste the text\n"
"where you placed the cursor. Note that you can copy and paste without ever\n"
"leaving the terminal you started. This makes posting the output of error\n"
"messages to the <uri link=\"http://forums.gentoo.org\">Gentoo Forums</uri>\n"
"extremely simple.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gpm.xml:169
#, no-wrap
msgid "Text-mode browsing and GPM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:173
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have a message on one screen and a text-mode web browser on the other,\n"
"you can copy the error message by highlighting it, then change to the other\n"
"terminal, left-click the appropriate text entry box to select it, and then\n"
"press the middle mouse button. Voil√†! Your error message can now be posted to\n"
"the forums.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:181
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Though discussion of text-only browsers is somewhat beyond the scope of this\n"
"guide, inevitably users will need to find a compatible console browser. Though\n"
"<c>lynx</c> is most likely the oldest and well established browser, its\n"
"interface has poor mouse support and recognition. Instead, try using\n"
"<c>links</c> which has excellent mouse integration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:188
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining links"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gpm.xml:189
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge links</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gpm.xml:193
#, no-wrap
msgid "This concludes the guide to using a mouse within the console. Happy mousing!\n"
msgstr ""
